Gov. Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has directed schools in Ibadan to resume normal academic activities from Monday. The state’s Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Mr Olasunkanmi Olaleye, made this known in a statement issued on Sunday in Ibadan. Olaleye said that the directive followed a review of the situation in the Ibadan metropolis as earlier promised by Gov. Makinde in a state broadcast on Oct. 20. The commissioner quoted the governor as appreciating youths who have been cooperating with security operatives to maintain peace. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Makinde, on Oct. 20, ordered the closure of all public and private schools within the Ibadan metropolis for three days. The governor had promised to review the situation on Oct. 23. Vanguard Gov. Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has directed schools in Ibadan to resume normal academic activities from Monday.   The state’s Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Mr Olasunkanmi Olaleye, made this known in a statement issued on Sunday in Ibadan. READ ALSO:#EndSARS Protests: Buhari condemns eviction notices to ethic,… October 25, 2020 In "News" Oyo State Governor, Mr Seyi Makinde, has directed schools in Ibadan, the state capital, to resume normal academic activities from Monday 26th October, 2020. The Honourable Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Mr Olasunkanmi Olaleye, who made this known in a statement issued on Sunday, said that the directive followed… October 25, 2020 In "Education" By Adeola Badru Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State, called on angry protesters to embrace peace, as they stormed Testing Ground Police Barracks, Idi-Ape, Ibadan to burn it down. While addressing the protesters along Iwo-Road, Governor Makinde appealed strongly for calm with a promised that government would look into their… October 22, 2020 In "News"